'''Bien-Air Medical Technologies''' develops, manufactures, and markets instrumentation devices and systems across multiple dental and surgery specialities. The company operates eight subsidiaries from its [[Bienne, Switzerland]] headquarters and is backed by a network of distributors, agents, and after-sales centers on all five continents.

Bien-Air was founded by David Mosimann in 1959 to develop medical instruments that would improve work for medical practitioners. They developed their first air-turbine dental drill in 1965. The first all electric dental drill in was developed by Bien-Air in 1970.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dental.bienair.com/en_us/about/|title=About Us - History|language=English|website=Bien-Air|accessdate=11 Aug 2017}}</ref>

