{{Other uses|Cloche (disambiguation){{!}}Cloche}} [[File:Victorian cloches in walled garden - geograph.org.uk - 1526721.jpg|thumb|upright|Cloches in a walled garden.]] In [[agriculture]] and [[gardening]], a '''cloche''' (from French, ''cloche'' for "bell") is a covering for protecting plants from cold temperatures. The original form of a cloche is a bell-shaped glass cover that is placed over an individual plant; modern cloches are usually made from [[plastic]]. The use of cloches is traced back to [[market garden]]s in 19th century [[France]], where entire fields of plants would be protected with cloches. In commercial growing, cloches have largely been replaced by [[row cover]], and nowadays are mainly found in smaller gardens.<ref name="cloches">{{cite web | url=http://www.garden.org/subchannels/edibles/veggies?q=show&id=546 | title=All About Cloches | publisher=National Gardening Association | accessdate=19 March 2015 | author=Reich, Lee}}</ref>
