{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox lake | name = Golyam Beglik reservoir | native_name = язовир Голям Беглик | image = Golyam Beglik Dam 7.jpg | caption = A view of the reservoir | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Pazardzhik Province]], [[Rhodope Mountains]] | coords = {{Coord|41|48|54|N|24|7|8|E|type:waterbody_region:BG}} | lake_type = [[reservoir]] | inflow = | outflow = | catchment = | basin_countries = [[Bulgaria]] | length = {{Convert|5.5|km|mi|abbr=on}} | width = {{Convert|5|km|mi|abbr=on}} | area = {{convert|4.1|km2|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = | volume = {{convert|62.1|e6m3|acre.ft|abbr=on}} | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | frozen = | islands = | cities = }}
'''Golyam Beglik''' is a reservoir near the central parts of the [[Rhodope Mountains]], [[Bulgaria]]. It was formerly officially called the '''Vasil Kolarov reservoir''' in honour of [[Vasil Kolarov]], a communist political leader of the [[People's Republic of Bulgaria]].
The reservoir [[Batak Dam|Batak]], [[Beglika]], [[Shiroka Polyana]] and Golyam Beglik are the main tourist places in the region of [[Batak, Bulgaria|Batak]]. The lakes are located to the north and to the south at high sea level.
There is a large diversity of game near the reservoir territory. There are [[bear]], [[deer]], [[fox]]es, [[wolf|wol]]ves, as well as smaller animals such as [[rabbit]]s, [[hedgehog]]s, [[squirrel]]s. There are also many wild [[duck]]s and geese near its water areas. The place is well suited for developing hunting tourism that is traditional in the region.
